      • call

        public static MethodCallExpression call​(Class clazz,
                                        String methodName,
                                        List<? extends Expression> arguments,
                                        Expression targetExpression)
        The powerful version of org.apache.calcite.linq4j.tree.Expressions#call( Type, String, Iterable<? extends Expression>). Try best effort to convert the accepted arguments to match parameter type.
        Parameters:
        clazz - Class against which method is invoked
        methodName - Name of method
        arguments - argument expressions
        targetExpression - target expression
        Returns:
        MethodCallExpression that call the given name method
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - if no suitable method found

      • sessionize

        public static Enumerable<Object[]> sessionize​(Enumerator<Object[]> inputEnumerator,
                                              int indexOfWatermarkedColumn,
                                              int indexOfKeyColumn,
                                              long gap)
        Creates enumerable implementation that applies sessionization to elements from the input enumerator based on a specified key. Elements are windowed into sessions separated by periods with no input for at least the duration specified by gap parameter.
